# Canonical author identity.
#
# Coalesces a stray plain-Gmail identity (which GitHub attributed to the duplicate
# account "Josrade") into the real account "YosefHayim". This is belt-and-suspenders
# next to the one-time history rewrite and the repo-local `user.email`: it keeps
# `git shortlog` / `git log --use-mailmap` and other tooling to a single identity if a
# commit ever lands under the plain address again.
#
# Format: <canonical name> <canonical email> <commit email to remap>
